FBIS4-367 "drafr069_e_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-069 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 WEST AFRICA Ghana Ministry Denies Soldiers Missing in Rwanda Ministry Denies Soldiers Missing in Rwanda AB0804182194 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in English 1800 GMT 8 Apr 94 AB0804182194 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network English BFN [Excerpt] The Ministry of Defense has denied reports that two Ghanaian soldiers serving with the UN Assistance Mission in Rwanda are missing. The reports say two Ghanaians and two Belgian observers could not be found. A statement issued in Accra today and signed by the director of the Public Relations Directorate of the Ghana Armed Forces, Colonel Akowia, said the commander of the Ghanaian contingent in the mission area has confirmed that no Ghanaian officer or man is missing. He added that they are all safe and sound. [passage omitted]
